feat(site): kill native tooltip, colour icons, detailed ack roles

Tooltip behaviour
- The native browser tooltip appeared below the cursor after a ~1s
  delay alongside the custom CSS tooltip, which was confusing. Fixed
  by moving abbr title -> aria-label in the sanitiser: browsers do
  not render a native tooltip from aria-label, screen readers still
  read the expansion, and the CSS tooltip reads content via
  attr(aria-label). Inline abbr fallbacks in index.html also
  title -> aria-label via sed so no-JS users get the same behaviour.

More abbr coverage
- pilot.p1: GDPR and APPI wrapped (EN / JA / FR); switched the HTML
  attr to data-i18n-html.
- how.p1: INRIA wrapped (EN / JA / FR).
- how.item_model: PyTorch wrapped (EN / JA / FR).
- Total abbr tags: 40 (en), 40 (ja), 39 (fr).

Coloured icons on team cards
- ORCID in ORCID green #A6CE39, LinkedIn in LinkedIn blue #0A66C2,
  Mail in Nagoya red (brand), using :has() selectors so no HTML
  changes required. Hover state fills the whole chip with the brand
  colour and white icon.

Acknowledgement roles
- All eight acknowledgees now show their actual role instead of just
  the affiliation, in EN / JA / FR:
  * Mrs Villers    -- Director, Research Department, Caen Univ. Hosp.
  * Mr Varnier     -- General Director, Caen Univ. Hosp.
  * Prof Lelong    -- Medical Head, Pharmacology, Caen Univ. Hosp.
  * Prof Parienti  -- Medical Head, Research Dept, Caen Univ. Hosp.
  * Dr Imaizumi    -- Lecturer, Clinical Research Education, NUGSM;
                       Dept of Nephrology, Nagoya Univ. Hospital
  * Prof Hashizume -- Professor, Advanced Medicine / Clinical Research
                       Education, Nagoya Univ. Hosp. & NUGSM
  * Prof Katsuno   -- Dean, Nagoya Univ. Graduate School of Medicine
  * Prof Kasuya    -- Vice-Dean for International Affairs, NUGSM

Layout
- Thanks cards switched from flex-row to a 2-column grid so the
  (now multi-line) role wraps cleanly beneath the name while the
  external-site arrow stays pinned to the right side of the card.

i18n parity preserved at 235 keys.
